# .env.example — VARIABLE NAMES ONLY, NEVER VALUES (§3.1, R10).
#
# Secrets are NOT read from this file at runtime. They live in the Windows Credential
# Manager via DPAPI (keyring) and are loaded by engine.core.secrets.Secrets (R10).
# Seed them once with:  python scripts/dpapi_set.py
#
# This file documents which secret keys + non-secret env vars the platform expects, so a
# `git grep` audit (Gate G0) can confirm no values were ever committed.

# ---- Secret keys stored in Windows Credential Manager (service: "market_trading") ----
# kite_api_key            # Kite Connect app API key
# kite_api_secret         # Kite Connect app API secret (checksum exchange, A5)
# kite_access_token       # daily access token (minted each trading day, expires ~06:00 IST, A5)
# telegram_bot_token      # Telegram bot token (O8)
# dashboard_token         # bearer token for the LAN dashboard + WS (R10)

# ---- Claude Agent SDK auth (D2/D11) ----
# The OAuth token is ALSO stored in Credential Manager (key: claude_code_oauth_token) and
# injected by the engine into the SDK CLI child's environment at startup (§2.2). It is NOT
# placed in a persistent user/service env var.
#   CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN   # minted via `claude setup-token` as the service user (D2)
#
# D2 TRAP: a stray ANTHROPIC_API_KEY silently OUTRANKS the OAuth token. The startup self-test
# asserts it is ABSENT unless owner deliberately enabled pay-as-you-go overflow (D6/§5.6).
#   ANTHROPIC_API_KEY         # leave UNSET on the Max-subscription path (D2)

# ---- Non-secret runtime overrides (optional; settings.yaml is the source of truth) ----
# MT_CONFIG_DIR           # override path to config/ (default: <repo>/config)
# MT_DATA_DIR             # override path to data/  (default: <repo>/data)
# MT_ENV                  # "dev" | "prod"  (default: dev)
